<scenario>
The agent A provided the following violation scenario:
The local variable 'impl' is declared as a non-const pointer (OS_impl_task_internal_record_t *impl) but in this function it is only used to read impl->id. Therefore it could and should be declared as a pointer to const (const OS_impl_task_internal_record_t *impl). The assignment impl = OS_OBJECT_TABLE_GET(...) yields a pointer to the table element (non-const), which can be implicitly converted to a pointer to const. Since no modification of *impl occurs here, not qualifying the pointer as pointing to const violates MISRA C 2023 Rule 8.13.
</scenario>
